[{"id":"VR855006","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three mirrors, labeled Mirror 1, Mirror 2, and Mirror 3. The three mirrors intersect at right angles such that they form the left, bottom, and right sides of a rectangle, with Mirror 1 vertical and to the left, Mirror 2 horizontal and on the bottom, and Mirror 3 vertical and to the right. A ray labeled “Incident Light Beam” slants downward from the right and towards Mirror 1, striking it in the interior of the rectangle. The angle between the ray and the horizontal is labeled theta sub 0 is less than 45 degrees. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR855006.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three mirrors, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>, are joined at right angles to make a shallow box, as shown in the figure. A beam of light is incident on Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> at an angle of incidence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 0\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 0\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> is less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"45 degrees\"><math alttext=\"45 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mn>45</mn><mo>∘</mo></msup></math></span></span>. After reflecting off of Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, the beam then reflects off of Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> and finally reflects off of Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares the angles of reflection <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 2\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 3\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></span></span> for the beam relative to mirrors <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>, respectively?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR855006_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1, equals theta sub 2, which equals theta sub 3\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1, equals theta sub 2, which equals theta sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, theta sub 1, equals theta sub 3, close parenthesis, is greater than theta sub 2\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, theta sub 1, equals theta sub 3, close parenthesis, is greater than theta sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mrow><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 2, is greater than open parenthesis, theta sub 1, equals theta sub 3, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 2, is greater than open parenthesis, theta sub 1, equals theta sub 3, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 3, is greater than theta sub 2, which is greater than theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 3, is greater than theta sub 2, which is greater than theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]